                    <comment id="12905527" author="cimjmoore" created="Thu, 2 Sep 2010 15:43:00 +0100"  >I&amp;#39;ve uploaded a patch that fixes this issue, including unit tests. One area for discussion is how to populate the comment section of the Via header (if we want to include one). Currently the implementation follows the format of the User-Agent set by DefaultHttpClient, so:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Via: 1.1 localhost (Apache-HttpClient/4.1-alpha3-SNAPSHOT (cache))&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This patch is contributed with the permission of my employer.</comment>
                    <comment id="12905671" author="olegk" created="Thu, 2 Sep 2010 22:08:41 +0100"  >Patch checked in. Many thanks, Jon&lt;br/&gt;
